(42, 11, 1, 45, 8, 26, 27, 'teach us to pray', 'Prayer and Divine Assistance', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer and the need for divine assistance in communicating with God. In Luke, the disciples seek guidance on how to pray, while Romans emphasizes the Spirit''s role in helping believers pray according to God''s will.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 1, 42, 22, 39, 45, NULL, 'Connection of Prayer and Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in times of distress. In Luke 11:1, the disciples seek guidance on prayer, while in Luke 22:39-45, Jesus models earnest prayer to resist temptation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 1, 65, 1, 20, 20, 'teach us to pray', 'Connection of Prayer in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer as a vital practice in the life of believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer, with Luke focusing on learning to pray and Jude encouraging prayer in the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 1, 42, 6, 12, 12, 'teach us to pray', 'Connection of Prayer Practices', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer in both passages. In Luke 11:1, the disciples seek to learn how to pray, while in Luke 6:12, Jesus models prayer by spending all night in prayer to God.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 1, 59, 4, 2, 3, 'teach us to pray', 'Connection Between Prayer and Asking', 'This connection highlights the importance of prayer and asking in both passages. Luke emphasizes the disciples'' request to learn how to pray, while James discusses the necessity of asking to receive, indicating that prayer is essential for fulfilling desires.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 1, 19, 10, 17, 17, 'teach us to pray', 'Connection of Prayer and Humility', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and the humble heart. Luke 11:1 shows the disciples seeking guidance on prayer, while Psalms 10:17 highlights God''s attentiveness to the desires of the humble.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 40, 6, 6, 15, 'Our Father which art in heaven', 'Connection in Prayer Instructions', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of addressing God as ''Our Father which art in heaven'' and include the phrase ''Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done, as in heaven, so in earth.'' This connection highlights a shared teaching on the nature of prayer and the relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 21, 5, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between God in heaven and humanity on earth. Luke 11:2 highlights God''s sovereignty with ''Thy will be done, as in heaven, so in earth,'' while Ecclesiastes 5:2 reminds us of our position with ''for God is in heaven, and thou upon earth.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 19, 72, 18, 19, 'Thy kingdom come', 'Divine Glory and Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the glory of God''s name and the establishment of His kingdom on earth. Luke 11:2''s plea for God''s kingdom aligns with Psalms 72:19''s desire for the earth to be filled with His glory.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 14, 20, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Sovereignty', 'Both passages emphasize God''s rule in heaven and over all kingdoms. They highlight the power and authority of God, affirming His sovereignty in prayer and worship.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 19, 11, 4, 4, 'Thy will be done, as in heaven, so in earth.', 'Heavenly Authority and Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s presence in heaven and His authority over earth. Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s will being done on earth as it is in heaven.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 52, 3, 11, 13, 'Our Father which art in heaven', 'Connection of Father and Holiness', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship with ''Our Father'' and the importance of holiness. Luke highlights the reverence due to God, while 1 Thessalonians speaks to being established in holiness before ''God, even our Father.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 2, 66, 15, 4, 4, 'Hallowed be thy name', 'Connection of Worship and Holiness', 'Both passages emphasize the holiness of God and the call for worship. Luke highlights the reverence due to God''s name, while Revelation speaks to the nations glorifying Him for His holiness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 3, 40, 6, 11, 11, 'daily bread', 'Connection of Daily Bread Requests', 'Both passages emphasize the request for daily sustenance, highlighting a common theme of reliance on God for provision. The phrasing in both verses reflects a similar structure and intent, reinforcing the importance of daily bread.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 3, 40, 6, 34, 34, 'Give us day by day our daily bread.', 'Daily Needs and Present Focus', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of focusing on daily needs rather than worrying about the future. ''Daily bread'' in Luke highlights the necessity of present sustenance, while Matthew advises against concern for tomorrow, suggesting that each day has its own challenges.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 3, 20, 30, 8, 8, 'daily bread', 'Provision and Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of daily sustenance. Luke 11:3''s request for ''daily bread'' parallels Proverbs 30:8''s plea for ''food convenient for me,'' highlighting a shared theme of reliance on God for daily provisions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 3, 2, 16, 15, 22, 'Give us day by day our daily bread', 'Provision of Daily Bread', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of daily sustenance provided by God. In Luke, the request for ''daily bread'' reflects the Israelites'' experience of gathering manna each day as described in Exodus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 3, 23, 33, 16, 16, NULL, 'Provision of Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize the provision of essential sustenance. Luke speaks of daily bread, while Isaiah assures that bread shall be given, highlighting a divine guarantee of nourishment.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 3, 43, 6, 27, 33, 'Give us day by day our daily bread.', 'Connection of Daily Bread and True Bread', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bread, with Luke referencing ''daily bread'' and John discussing ''the true bread from heaven.'' This connection highlights the transition from physical sustenance to spiritual nourishment provided by Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 40, 6, 12, 15, 'forgive us our sins; for we also forgive', 'Forgiveness and Temptation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of forgiveness and the request to be delivered from evil. They share similar phrases regarding forgiveness and temptation, highlighting a common theme in the teachings of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 40, 26, 41, 41, 'lead us not into temptation', 'Temptation and Prayer Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of avoiding temptation through prayer. Luke highlights the need for deliverance from evil, while Matthew encourages vigilance in prayer to resist temptation.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 23, 43, 25, 26, 'forgive us our sins', 'Forgiveness and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of forgiveness and deliverance from sin. Luke highlights the need for forgiveness and protection from evil, while Isaiah speaks of God blotteth out transgressions and not remembering sins.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 51, 3, 13, 13, 'forgive every one that is indebted to us', 'Forgiveness and Mutual Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of forgiveness among individuals. Luke highlights the need to forgive debts, while Colossians encourages forgiving one another as Christ forgave.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 53, 3, 3, 3, 'deliver us from evil', 'Connection of Deliverance from Evil', 'Both passages emphasize deliverance from evil, with Luke 11:4 requesting protection from evil and 2 Thessalonians 3:3 affirming the Lord''s faithfulness in keeping believers from evil. This thematic parallel highlights the importance of divine protection in the lives of the faithful.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 49, 4, 31, 32, 'forgive every one that is indebted to us', 'Forgiveness and Kindness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of forgiveness. Luke 11:4 highlights the need to forgive others as a condition for receiving forgiveness, while Ephesians 4:32 encourages kindness and forgiveness among individuals, mirroring this principle.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 4, 59, 2, 13, 13, 'forgive every one that is indebted to us', 'Connection of Mercy and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of mercy and forgiveness. Luke highlights the need to forgive others to receive forgiveness, while James warns that judgment without mercy awaits those who do not show mercy.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 5, 42, 18, 1, 8, NULL, 'Persistence in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of persistence in seeking help. In Luke 11:5, the friend seeks bread at midnight, while in Luke 18:1-8, the widow persistently seeks justice from the judge.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 7, 40, 25, 10, 10, 'the door is now shut', 'Shut Door Motif', 'This connection highlights the theme of a closed door representing exclusion. Both passages emphasize the finality of the door being shut, indicating a barrier to access.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 7, 42, 7, 6, 6, 'Trouble me not', 'Connection of Worthiness and Trouble', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of worthiness and the reluctance to trouble others. In Luke 11:7, the speaker expresses a desire not to be troubled, while in Luke 7:6, the centurion similarly asks Jesus not to trouble himself, highlighting a shared sentiment of humility and respect.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 7, 42, 13, 25, 25, 'the door is now shut', 'Closed Door Motif', 'This connection highlights the theme of a closed door in both passages. In Luke 11:7, the door is shut, and in Luke 13:25, the master has also shut the door, emphasizing the finality of rejection.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
